{# Message shown when there are open work items and user is idle.

Variables:
  - task_count: Number of ready work items
  - idle_minutes: Minutes since user was last active
#}
# Open Work Items Available

There {% if task_count == 1 %}is 1 work item{% else %}are {{ task_count }} work items{% endif %} ready to work on.

The user hasn't been active for {{ idle_minutes }} minutes. Rather than stopping, please continue working on the available items.

## What to do

1. Use `list_tasks` to see what needs to be done
2. Pick a work item and use `work_on` to start working on it
3. Complete the work item and mark it as done
4. Continue with other items or stop when you're blocked

If you genuinely need user input, use the `create_question` tool to ask and link it to the relevant work item.
